  "rollout_plan_displayname": "Will ship enabled for all users",
  "motivation": "Currently, deletion keyboard shortcuts like Ctrl+Backspace in contenteditable elements always report deleteWordBackward in beforeinput and input events, even when deleting selected text. The W3C Input Events specification requires deleteContentBackward for non-collapsed selections and deleteWordBackward only for collapsed selections (caret with no selection). This change aligns Chrome with the specification by reporting deleteContentBackward/Forward when text is selected and deleteWordBackward/Forward when operating at a caret position.",
